{"questionId":"9736","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>Helen is building a cabin using cylindrical logs of length 2.4 m and radius 8.4 cm. A wedge is&nbsp;cut from one log and the cross-section of this log is illustrated in the following diagram.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><img src=\"__IMG__/7afd8773bb68ce161933819a579c6e52c784e18e.png\"></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Find&nbsp;50° in radians.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\frac{{50 \\times \\pi }}{{180}} = 0.873\\,\\,\\left( {0.872664 \\ldots } \\right)\"> <mfrac> <mrow> <mn>50</mn> <mo>×</mo> <mi>π</mi> </mrow> <mrow> <mn>180</mn> </mrow> </mfrac> <mo>=</mo> <mn>0.873</mn> <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace> <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace> <mrow> <mo>(</mo> <mrow> <mn>0.872664</mn> <mo>…</mo> </mrow> <mo>)</mo> </mrow> </math></span>&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><em><strong>[1 mark]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"9736","referenceCode":"SPM.1.AHL.TZ0.5a","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"Find 50° in radians.","paper":"1","level":"HL","questionNumber":"a","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 3—Geometry and trigonometry","Topic 3—Geometry and trigonometry","AHL 3.7—Radians"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}